The paper deals with the storage of binary cycles in neural networks, specifically Hopfield-type networks, and investigates the role of network connectivities in generating cyclic patterns. This falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the topology of the corresponding networks, which could be classified under systems and control (cs.SY) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the simulations presented in the paper involve spiking neurons, which could be classified under signal processing (cs.SI).
